Java 21 ‚Äì Sequenced Collections (One-Page Notes)
1Ô∏è‚É£ What is a Sequenced Collection?

A Sequenced collection is an ordered collection that:

Has a well-defined first and last element

Supports a reversed view

May (but need not) support insertion/removal at both ends

Sequenced ‚â† Deque
Sequenced is about order awareness, not mandatory double-ended mutation.

2Ô∏è‚É£ Interfaces Introduced in Java 21

| Interface                | Description                                 |
| ------------------------ | ------------------------------------------- |
| `SequencedCollection<E>` | Base interface for ordered collections      |
| `SequencedSet<E>`        | Sequenced collection with **no duplicates** |
| `SequencedMap<K,V>`      | Sequenced key-value map                     |


3Ô∏è‚É£ Conditions to be Sequenced (MUST KNOW)

A collection is sequenced if it satisfies ALL:

Predictable order

Insertion order or

Sorted order

First & Last element are well-defined

Reversible view exists

‚ö† Supporting insertion/removal at both ends is optional

4Ô∏è‚É£ Common Methods (Very Important)

üîπ SequencedCollection<E>
E getFirst();
E getLast();

void addFirst(E e);
void addLast(E e);

E removeFirst();
E removeLast();

SequencedCollection<E> reversed();


üîπ SequencedMap<K,V>

Map.Entry<K,V> firstEntry();
Map.Entry<K,V> lastEntry();

void putFirst(K key, V value);
void putLast(K key, V value);

Map.Entry<K,V> pollFirstEntry();
Map.Entry<K,V> pollLastEntry();

SequencedMap<K,V> reversed();


5Ô∏è‚É£ Collections Supporting Sequenced Feature

‚úÖ SequencedCollection

| Collection | Order     |
| ---------- | --------- |
| `List`     | Insertion |
| `Deque`    | Insertion |

‚úÖ SequencedSet

| Collection      | Order     | Notes                |
| --------------- | --------- | -------------------- |
| `LinkedHashSet` | Insertion | Full support         |
| `TreeSet`       | Sorted    | `addFirst/addLast` ‚ùå |

‚úÖ SequencedMap

| Collection      | Order     | Notes                |
| --------------- | --------- | -------------------- |
| `LinkedHashMap` | Insertion | Full support         |
| `TreeMap`       | Sorted    | `putFirst/putLast` ‚ùå |


6Ô∏è‚É£ Collections NOT Sequenced ‚ùå
| Collection      | Reason                   |
| --------------- | ------------------------ |
| `HashSet`       | No order                 |
| `HashMap`       | No order                 |
| `Hashtable`     | No order                 |
| `Queue`         | No first/last control    |
| `PriorityQueue` | No predictable iteration |

9Ô∏è‚É£ One-Line Interview Summary ‚≠ê

Sequenced collections unify ordered collections by providing common first/last and reverse operations, while allowing implementations to restrict unsupported mutations.

üîü Memory Trick (Best One)

Sequenced = Knows order
Deque = Controls order